Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 30. Name probably Diopeithes. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0188.44.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1703)
